message.content: This question requires knowledge about which organisms are capable of photosynthesis. Photosynthesis is a process carried out by plants, algae, and some bacteria, not animals. Photosynthesis is a process carried out by plants, algae, and some bacteria, where carbon dioxide and water are converted into glucose and oxygen using energy from sunlight. Therefore, the only option that is a plant is option (C), a willow. Options (A), (B), and (D) are all animals and do not have the ability to photosynthesize.
